news.title: TA Associates leads $400 million investment in Vastu Housing Finance
news.para: Financial details of the transaction were not disclosed. People familiar with the matter said the investors bought the stake for about ₹3,340 crore ($400 million) and it valued Vastu at ₹10,000 crore.

news.title: Bombay HC refuses bail to Radius Group's MD in Yes Bank-DHFL case
news.para: According to the prosecution, in March 2020, CBI had registered an FIR under the IPC and Prevention of Corruption Act against Yes Bank founder Rana Kapoor, DHFL promoters Kapil and Dheeraj Wadhawan and others.

news.title: Supertech files resolution plan to Greater Noida authority to clear Rs 900 crore dues
news.para: These three projects are in the ambit of insolvency proceedings that were initiated by the National Company Law Tribunal (NCLT) against the group company, Supertech Ltd, on March 25, 2022.

news.title: Haryana CM distributes property certificates to 5,000 people in Manesar
news.para: Many individuals had property in urban areas but lacked ownership rights. Numerous disputes were ongoing in court, creating an atmosphere of fear among people that they might lose their property, he said.

news.title: Keystone Realtors acquires 88 acres land in Thane for Rs 91 crore
news.para: The total consideration for the land purchase is Rs 91 crore, with Rs 1 crore already paid and the remaining Rs 90 crore to be paid in a staggered manner over the next two years.

news.title: Bombay HC upholds Maharashtra government decision to increase lease rent in Bandra
news.para: The court on July 10 (Wednesday) disposed of a bunch of petitions filed by several housing societies in Bandra challenging the government resolutions of 2006, 2012 and 2018 revising the rent on long-term leases granted to them.

news.title: RKN Enterprises sells 1.43% stake in Godrej Properties for Rs 1,320.90 crore
news.para: Additionally, RKN Enterprises also sold 39.86 lakh shares, amounting to a 1.43 per cent stake in Godrej Properties. The shares were disposed of at an average price of Rs 3,313.90 apiece, taking the deal value to Rs 1,320.90 crore.

news.title: Builders expect sale of distressed properties to rise in Hong Kong in Q2 FY25
news.para: An increasing acceptance among lenders and landlords to book steeper losses has driven up the number of these deals in a market forecast to remain lacklustre due to the higher interest rates and falling rental income, realtors said.

news.title: Demand for high-end properties in Britain dented by tax policies: Winkworth
news.para: Britain's tight national finances have for some time meant there is little scope to invest government money in improving its ailing public services.

news.title: Hong Kong regulators partially clears PwC of alleged deficiencies in Evergrande audits
news.para: Heavily indebted Evergrande became the poster child of the years-long crisis in China's real estate market, and its onshore unit was accused of a $78 billion revenue overstatement in March.

news.title: Sebi set to auction HBN Dairies' properties in August 2024
news.para: This came after the Supreme Court in its order dated May 14, 2024, authorised Sebi to sell the assets of HBN Dairies & Allied Ltd (HBN) with the active involvement of the liquidator.

news.title: Kriti Sanon buys 2,000 sq ft land in Alibaug
news.para: The recently inaugurated MTHL connectivity further enhances convenience, making this project an even more attractive choice for those seeking a sophisticated retreat in Alibaug's real estate landscape.

news.title: Retail space demand rises by 15% in shopping malls in Q1 FY25: Report
news.para: As per the data, the leasing activities in shopping malls rose to 6,12,396 square feet during April-June 2024 from 5,33,078 square feet in the year-ago period.

news.title: Proptech startup Jugyah raises $1.5 million in funding
news.para: With the fresh funds, the Mumbai-based company plans to expand its reach within the Mumbai Metropolitan Region and increase its market share.

news.title: Prestige Estate reports drop in sales by 23% in Q1 FY25
news.para: In a regulatory filing, Prestige Estates said the company sold 2.86 million square feet in April-June against 3.83 million square feet in the corresponding period of the previous year.

news.title: Bengaluru metro gears up for extension of green line
news.para: Bengaluru Metro Rail Corporation Limited (BMRCL) is gearing up for the much-awaited launch of the 3.7 km Nagasandra to Madavara metro stretch on the Green Line.

news.title: Piramal Capital & Housing Finance raises Rs 835 crore through social loan
news.para: The loan has a three-year maturity, and it is benchmarked to the three-month secured overnight financing rate (SOFR) plus 200 basis points. The prevailing SOFR is 5.3%.

news.title: Sanofi India decides to put 1.5 lakh sq ft headquarter in Mumbai on the block
news.para: The company has already picked up an office in Vikhroli suburb through a long-term lease to shift one of its divisions Sanofi Consumer Healthcare and is in the process of leasing additional space for growth as well as relocation of other operations.

news.title: UltraTech Cement acquires additional 25% stake in UAE-based RAKWCT
news.para: The acquisition was made by UltraTech Cement Middle East Investments Ltd (UCMEIL), a wholly-owned subsidiary of the Indian cement maker in the UAE.

news.title: No project can fail if builders maintain financial discipline: Haryana RERA member
news.para: "There is a need of rationalisation of interest rates, lending rates, because once the lending rates are reduced, certainly the investors or the homebuyers come forward. And builders are also happy to deliver at least possible costs," Arora said.
